This is the moment an armed robber burst into a North Tyneside store with a handgun, stole the store's money then apologised to the shopkeeper before running off.

Police now are hunting the masked raider after the attack, which happened just before 7am yesterday at Diane's Newsagency, in Angle Terrace, Wallsend.

The 46-year-old member of staff, Jeanette Greenwell, from Wallsend, was shocked but otherwise uninjured.

