'I think it's quite risky of the guy to pull a stunt like that all for the sake of £80.'

Police are now appealing for witnesses or anyone with information to contact them as soon as possible.

Police Chief Inspector Steve Readdie, of North Tyneside Area Command, said: 'We have extra officers on patrol in the area to reassure residents and answer any concerns people may have.'

Anyone with information should contact police on 101, extension 69191, quoting log number 166 of 06/02/15 or ring the independent charity Crimestoppers on 0800 555 111.

